                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/7695: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-06T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 6, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 6—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>544. An official of the Foreign Office has confirmed the press report that the
                    Spanish Embassy at Paris delivered a note last night to the French Government
                    reviewing the situation in Spain, particularly with regard to nonintervention,
                    and requesting the permission of the French Government to buy arms in France.
                    The official stated that the Foreign Office was studying this matter prior to
                    deciding what reply to make.</p>
                <p>He indicated that this request was embarrassing to the French Government due on
                    the one hand to the pressure of left political parties here to have France
                    intervene in Spain and on the other hand to the attitude of England in support
                    of nonintervention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
